Write a program to reverse a 3-digit number.

Input Format

Input consists of an integer.

Constraints

NA

Output Format

The output will be the reverse of the input integers.

Sample Input 0

456
Sample Output 0

654
Sample Input 1

123
Sample Output 1

321

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>


    
int main() 
{
    int n;
    int first,second,last,ans;
    scanf("%d",&n);
    first=n%10;
    second = (n/10)%10;
    last=n/100;
    ans = (first*100)+(second*10)+last;
    printf("%d",ans);    
    return 0;
}
